<p>Hurricane Melissa strengthened into a Category 5 storm and approached Jamaica on Monday-Tuesday, with forecasters warning of life‑threatening winds, storm surge and catastrophic rainfall that could linger because the system is moving unusually slowly . Officials ordered mandatory evacuations for tens of thousands of residents and travelers as governments prepared emergency response measures; the storm has already been blamed for deaths in the Caribbean islands . Meteorologists say Melissa rapidly intensified while drifting over unusually warm Caribbean waters, increasing its size and destructive potential and complicating forecasts for rainfall and surge .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/AvdELaa9llZaW6xWmfR33NrntvjvOJW4HeIgnGk0ArNyw-RLbzXOC39j_v1ZUmzA1ORt7212KlJJQup8CbaDJGnSmP1ISOw6HOqsb1peQvtvSfFJFD4Edo9cqF7T7G-jGmNo7Ql11CUnh5ZjbhfC6k8K2nfUxNNSbnhobhifsnfiWBPqayTHSabUsuLbLu6M10d8mEE7' alt='A fallen tree in Kingston, Jamaica, on Monday as Hurricane Melissa drew closer.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Data flights: U.S. Air Force &#x27;Hurricane Hunters&#x27; flew reconnaissance missions into Melissa’s eye to collect measurements that feed National Hurricane Center forecasts .</li><li>Shelter capacity: Authorities opened more than 800 emergency shelters across Jamaica to receive evacuees as officials urged people to move inland from vulnerable coastal zones .</li><li>Tourism disruption: Resorts and beach towns scrambled: stranded visitors boarded windows and staff prepared for major property damage to hotels that drive much of Jamaica’s economy .</li><li>Forecast challenges: Melissa’s slow forward speed — just a few miles per hour — increases rainfall totals and landslide risk, complicating timing of evacuations and response .</li></ul><blockquote>There is no infrastructure in the region that can withstand a Category 5. The question now is the speed of recovery - Andrew Holness</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Jamaican government: Prime Minister Andrew Holness warned that no local infrastructure can withstand a Category 5 storm and emphasized rapid recovery will be a major challenge. (<a href='https://english.elpais.com/climate/2025-10-28/hurricane-melissa-bears-down-on-jamaica-as-its-strongest-storm-in-recorded-history.html'>elpais.com</a>)</li><li>National Hurricane Center / meteorologists: Forecasters say Melissa’s slow movement over unusually warm Caribbean waters helped it balloon in size and intensity, raising flood and landslide risks. (<a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/10/27/nx-s1-5587928/hurricane-melissa-jamaica-cuba-category-5'>npr.org</a>)</li><li>Local residents: Many Jamaicans expressed fear and faith as they sought shelter and waited out the storm, asking for safety and quick recovery. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/28/jamaica-braces-for-hurricane-melissa-islands-strongest-storm-on-record'>aljazeera.com</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/10/27/nx-s1-5587928/hurricane-melissa-jamaica-cuba-category-5'>Why Hurricane Melissa&#x27;s intensity and slow-moving speed are a recipe for disaster</a> - npr.org</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/oct/27/jamaicans-take-shelter-as-hurricane-melissa-bears-down-as-category-5-storm'>Jamaicans take shelter as Hurricane Melissa bears down as category 5 storm</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/hurricane-melissa-jamaica-updates-october-28-2025/article70210957.ece'>Hurricane Melissa begins lashing Jamaica as &#x27;catastrophic&#x27; Category 5 storm</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/live/2025/10/28/weather/hurricane-melissa-jamaica-landfall'>Live Updates: Jamaica Warns Hurricane Melissa Will Bring Catastrophic Winds and Rain</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/environment/article/2025/10/28/jamaica-braces-for-mass-destruction-as-hurricane-melissa-churns-in_6746840_114.html'>Hurricane Meliss